title: "Ordinative Sciences Framework: Technology of Expressions (TE) for Anti-Bias AI Formulations"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-03-27
url: "https://github.com/anckhalion/ordinative_sciences_framework"
repository-code: "https://github.com/anckhalion/ordinative_sciences_framework"
abstract: >-
  The TE Framework represents a structural ontology of meaning, formally defined as Ordinative Set Theory (OST). 
  It provides an alternative to probability-based NLP and LLM alignment (RLHF) by establishing vectors of structural 
  coherence and phase-shift diagnostics (Controfase) to detect and resolve narrative capture, projective voids, 
  and epistemic cowardice in computational processing.
keywords:
